cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.AI, cs.NE 

This paper deals with incorporating temporal information into Spatial Convolutional Neural Networks (ConvNets) for video analysis. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses weight initialization strategies, which falls under the category of machine learning, hence cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely. Additionally, the paper deals with video analysis, which can be categorized under cs.MM (Multimedia). The paper also proposes a new way of incorporating temporal information, which can be considered as an advancement in Artificial Intelligence, hence cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely. Finally, the paper discusses the importance of initializing weights judiciously, which can be considered as a neural network optimization problem, hence cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is also a likely category.
